=======================================================================
FILES
=======================================================================

  c45.py          — C4.5 class implementation + load_csv utility
  InduceC45.py    — Decision tree induction program
  predict.py      — Prediction program
  crossVal.py     — 10-fold cross-validation (our C4.5)
  crossValSKL.py  — 10-fold cross-validation (scikit-learn)

=======================================================================
DEPENDENCIES
=======================================================================

  Python 3.8+
  pandas
  scikit-learn

Install with: pip install pandas scikit-learn

=======================================================================
RUNNING THE PROGRAMS
=======================================================================

1. Induce a decision tree (trains on full file, prints JSON to stdout):

     python InduceC45.py <TrainingSetFile.csv>
     python InduceC45.py <TrainingSetFile.csv> <fileToSave.json>

   Example:
     python InduceC45.py iris.data.csv iris_tree.json

2. Make predictions using a saved tree:

     python predict.py <CSVFile> <JSONFile>
     python predict.py <CSVFile> <JSONFile> eval

   Without "eval": prints one predicted class per line.
   With "eval": also prints accuracy, error rate, and confusion matrix.

   Example:
     python predict.py iris.data.csv iris_tree.json eval

3. 10-fold cross-validation with hyperparameter grid search (our C4.5):

     python crossVal.py <CSVFile> <HyperparamFile.json>
     python crossVal.py <CSVFile> <HyperparamFile.json> <outputTreeFile.json>

   HyperparamFile.json format:
     { "InfoGain": [0.0, 0.01, 0.05, ...], "Ratio": [0.0, 0.01, ...] }

   Example:
     python crossVal.py iris.data.csv hyperparams.json best_tree.json

4. 10-fold cross-validation with scikit-learn (Information Gain only):

     python crossValSKL.py <CSVFile> <HyperparamFile.json>
     python crossValSKL.py <CSVFile> <HyperparamFile.json> <outputTreeFile.txt>

   Example:
     python crossValSKL.py iris.data.csv hyperparams.json skl_tree.txt

=======================================================================
NOTES
=======================================================================

- All CSV files must use the 3-line header format described in the lab
  spec (column names / type codes / class variable name).
- The c45 class defaults to metric='gain_ratio' and threshold=0.0.
  InduceC45.py uses these defaults unless extended.
- For large datasets (e.g., letter-recognition) the cross-validation
  grid search may take 20-30 minutes to complete.
